    <main class="about">
      <h1>
        Go Izumita / 泉田剛
      </h1>

      <h2>
        Artist / Architectural Designer
      </h2>

      <p>
        Born in 2001 in Hirosaki,
        Aomori, Japan. After graduating
        from the Department of
        Architecture at Musashino Art
        University, I worked in 3DCG
        production at Shigeru Ban
        Architects.
      </p>

      <p>
        I am currently engaged in a
        practice that transforms
        abandoned and unused
        structures into sculptural works
        through processes of dismantling
        and reconstruction. By
        reassigning materials from these
        structures, my work explores the
        relationship between material,
        memory, and space.
      </p>

      <p>
        Alongside this practice, I support
        a wide range of projects through
        my expertise in graphic design.
        Moving fluidly between
        three-dimensional and
        two-dimensional media, as well
        as between architecture and
        graphic design, I explore new
        modes of expression that
        transcend conventional scales
        and disciplinary boundaries.
      </p>

      <h2>
        v Awards & Honors
